Hi,

I don't recall how long it takes to find a solution to the
11-multipexer. I did a run overnight and started another one this
morning, neither of these two runs has found a solution yet. So the
best answer I can give right now is that it takes a non-trivial amount
of time on average - we're talking 1+ days of CPU time with SharpNEAT,
the run I'm doing now is at 5.5M evaluations and 7000 generations.

I use a population of 1000, the target number of species is between 40
and 50. The activation function is SharpNEAT's default, the 'Steepened
Sigmoid':

y = 1/(1+exp(-4.9*x))


Regarding Mono - last time I tried it with SharpNEAT it was a
straightforward and painless exercise. Just type 'mono SharpNEAT.exe'
at the command line. I think there was a bug or two in the GUI as I
clicked around but it was essentially all working fine without any
messing about.

Hope that helps, I'll post again with an update from the current run.

Colin
